/*In a chat application, a user types a message that needs to be displayed in reverse. Write a Java program to
reverse the given string. First, solve the problem by accessing each character using the charAt() method and
a loop. Then, solve the same problem using the StringBuffer class and its reverse() method for a more efficient
solution.*/

package Exercise_3;

import java.util.*;

public class reverseUsing_charAt {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter message: ");
		String s = sc.nextLine();
		System.out.println("Reversed Message: ");
		for(int i=s.length()-1;i>=0;i--)
			System.out.print(s.charAt(i));
		sc.close();
	}
}
